{
  "stem": "14928.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she'll take me to a village where I could survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I could work for them, for the people in the village.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this is the way I got out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time already, people were working.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Warsaw boys, from Warsaw, made passport.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They redid my passport from a Ukrainian passport-- a Russian passport to a Ukrainian passport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't have already my Jewish name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I already had Katya and Sekeluk instead of Sekel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So and this is when I had this passport.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this woman came.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She send her daughter, with a baby, one day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was-- the daughter's married name, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her maiden name was Lugosz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her father's name was Jan Lugosz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't-- don't remember exactly, was it Maria, her mother's name?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I really don't remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I didn't see her too many times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I saw her just once over there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- because he said, this is the woman that's going to take you to that-- to the village.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- but she figured, if her daughter comes, and she's young, and she'll give-- she gave me the baby, to carry the baby through the gate.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I passed through the gate with the baby.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had-- these people, my friends, Landsberg, he worked there in the-- in the school where they sorted out the Jewish-- the clothes that they killed the ghettos out-- the Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used to take the clothes, the gold, just everything there, what they had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they took people to sort it out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by sorting out, they used to, every day, when we went home-- I worked there, too, for a few days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we were home, they-- he would look.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
